\begin{equation}
2Z6 = 6 + 10 \cdot 2 - 2^2
\end{equation}

We first calculate the term $10 \cdot 2$, which equals 20. We then calculate $2^2$, which equals 4. Next, we add our first term, 6, to 20, getting 26. Lastly, we subtract 4 from 26:

\begin{equation}
2Z6 = 6 + 20 - 4 = 26 - 4 = 22
\end{equation}

Thus, the value of the operation $2Z6$ is found to be 22 after performing the above calculations.

