10^{0.5+0.3+0.2+0.1+0.9} &= 10^{2.0}.
\end{align*} Since any number raised to the power of 2 is that number squared, in this case, \begin{align*}
10^{2} &= 10 \times 10 \\
&= 100. 
\end{align*} Therefore, the simplified expression is the integer 100, which we represent with the numeral inside a box for clarity and emphasis, as it is typically done in a mathematical context: \begin{align*}
&=\boxed{100}.
\end{align*} Final Answer: 100.0

