answer:
Translating the given information into mathematical equations to model the problem, the equations corresponding to the given conditions can be formulated as follows:
\begin{align*}
a + b + c &= 60, &\text{(The sum of } a, b, \text{ and } c \text{ is 60)} \\
a - 7 &= N, &\text{(Decreasing } a \text{ by 7 yields } N) \\
b + 7 &= N, &\text{(Increasing } b \text{ by 7 also yields } N) \\
7c &= N. &\text{(And } c \text{ times 7 is likewise } N)
\end{align*}

To determine the value of each variable $a$, $b$, and $c$ in terms of the unknown quantity $N$, each equation is solved respectively for the corresponding variable, yielding:
\begin{align*}
a &= N + 7, &\text{(from } a - 7 = N) \\
b &= N - 7, &\text{(from } b + 7 = N) \\
c &= \frac{N}{7}. &\text{(as } 7c = N)
\end{align*}

Having expressed $a$, $b$, and $c$ in terms of $N$, we substitute these values back into the first equation $\left( a + b + c = 60 \right)$ to find the value of $N$. Performing the substitution gives the following:
\begin{align*}
(N + 7) + (N - 7) + \left(\frac{N}{7}\right) = 60.
\end{align*}

Combining terms simplifies the equation to:
\begin{align*}
2N + \frac{N}{7} &= 60,\\
\frac{14N + N}{7} &= 60, &\text{(Finding a common denominator for } N \text{ terms)}\\
\frac{15N}{7} &= 60, &\text{(Combining the } N \text{ terms)}\\
15N &= 420, &\text{(Multiplying both sides by 7 to clear the fraction)}\\
N &= \frac{420}{15}, &\text{(Dividing both sides by 15 to solve for } N)\\
N &= 28. &\text{(Simplifying the fraction)}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the value of $N$ that satisfies all given conditions is $28$.

Final Answer: 28.0

