\begin{align*}
2b + s &= 210 \\
b + 2s &= 240 \\
\end{align*}

We are solving for $s$, so we want to eliminate $b$ from the equations above. Multiplying both sides of the second equation by 2, we get $2b+4s = 480$, or $2b = 480 - 4s$. Substituting this equation into the first equation above to eliminate $b$, we get that $(480 - 4s) + s = 210$, or $s=90$. Thus, a soda costs $\boxed{90}$ cents. Final Answer: 90

